{"id":"foreigner","term":"Foreigner","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A Gentile. Such as resided among the Hebrews were required by the law to be treated with kindness (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 22:21\">Ex. 22:21</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 23:9\">23:9</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Leviticus 19:33\">Lev. 19:33</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 2:3\">34</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 24:2\">23:22</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 14:28\">Deut. 14:28</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 16:10\">16:10</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 16:11\">11</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 24:19\">24:19</a>). They enjoyed in many things equal rights with the native-born residents (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 12:49\">Ex. 12:49</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Leviticus 24:22\">Lev. 24:22</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 15:15\">Num. 15:15</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 35:15\">35:15</a>), but were not allowed to do anything which was an abomination according to the Jewish law (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 20:10\">Ex. 20:10</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Leviticus 17:15\">Lev. 17:15</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:16\">16</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 18:26\">18:26</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 20:2\">20:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 24:16\">24:16</a>, etc.).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Exodus 22:21","Exodus 23:9","Leviticus 19:33","Genesis 2:3","Genesis 24:2","Deuteronomy 14:28","Deuteronomy 16:10","Deuteronomy 16:11","Deuteronomy 24:19","Exodus 12:49","Leviticus 24:22","Numbers 15:15","Numbers 35:15","Exodus 20:10","Leviticus 17:15","Genesis 1:16","Genesis 18:26","Genesis 20:2","Genesis 24:16"]}